  <title>Cogl.wayland_onscreen_set_foreign_surface</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function wayland_onscreen_set_foreign_surface(onscreen: <link xref="Cogl.Onscreen">Cogl.Onscreen</link>, surface: void): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_wayland_onscreen_set_foreign_surface()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Allows you to explicitly notify Cogl of an existing Wayland surface to use,
which prevents Cogl from allocating a surface and shell surface for the
<code>onscreen</code>. An allocated surface will not be destroyed when the <code>onscreen</code> is
freed.</p>  <p>This function must be called before <code>onscreen</code> is allocated.</p>
  <p>Since 1.16</p>
